fields.description: Space scientific experiment on board Sich-2
Ionospheric scientific project on Sich-1M satellite (2004-2005 years)

Eave probe WZ1 measured the AC X-component of the magnetic field and current density YZ component. Sensor axis is parallel to the X axis.  The normal to the probe gap angled 45 ° relative to the axes Y and Z, therefore this sensor measured inclined projection of the current vector.
fields.title: Wave probe WZ1

fields.description: Wave probe WZ2 measured the AC Y-component of the magnetic field and current density XZ component. Sensor axis is parallel to the Y axis.  The normal to the probe gap angled 45 ° relative to the axes X and Z, therefore this sensor measured inclined projection of the current vector.
fields.title: Wave probe WZ2

fields.description:
Electric probe complex consists of 4 electric probes located on separate beams: EZ1, EZ2, EZ3, EZ4. In order to obtain the three components of the electric field, sensor signals of EZ1, EZ2, EZ3, EZ4 were fed through a switch to the inputs of the differential amplifier to subtract. EZ1 or EZ3 were selected as a base sensor therefore there are 6 channels of electric field:
E1=EZ1-EZ4,   E2=EZ1-EZ2,   E3=EZ1-EZ3;
E4=EZ3-EZ1,   E5=EZ3-EZ2,   E6=EZ3-EZ4.
Coordinates of electric probe are: EZ1 (2.687, 2.687, 0.340), EZ2 (-2.828, -2.828, 0.260), EZ3 (0.168, -0.675, 4.280), EZ4 (2.100, -3.300, 0.375) meters in coordinate system associated with the satellite.
fields.title: Electric probe complex EZ

fields.description: The FC1 sensor is located above the probe FC2 along Z-axis and its window is facing upward.

fields.description: This device has as output the current-voltage characteristics from which ITM team can obtain a plasma density and an electron temperature.
fields.title: Plasma parameters sensor ECP

fields.description: The FC2 sensor is located below the probe FC2 along Z-axis and its window is facing downward.
